  <h1>
   gpu_get_state
  </h1>
  This function will get the current GPU state, returning it as a
  <a href="../../Data_Structures/DS_Maps/DS_Maps.htm">
   DS Map
  </a>
  . This can then be manipulated or even saved, and you can return this map to the GPU using the function
  <a href="gpu_set_state.htm">
   <span>
    gpu_set_state()
   </span>
  </a>
  .
  <h4>
   Syntax:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gpu_get_state();
</code></pre>
  <h4>
   Returns:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml"><a href="../../../../../GameMaker_Language/GML_Reference/Data_Structures/DS_Maps/ds_map_create.htm">
 DS Map ID
</a></code></pre>
  <h4>
   Example:
  </h4>
  <pre><code class="language-gml">gpu_map = gpu_get_state();
</code></pre>
  The above code stores the current GPU state in a variable.
 </body>
